div2.sp:
All.Kneeling
No man shed tears for noble Mutius;
He lives in fame that died in virtue's cause.

sp.l:
Yes, and will nobly him remunerate.
Flourish.
Re-enter, from one side, SATURNINUS attended, TAMORA, DEMETRIUS, CHIRON, and AARON;
from the other, BASSIANUS,
LAVINIA, and others.

sp.p:
Alas, sir, I know not Jupiter;
I never
drank with him in all my life.

div2.stage:
Enter SATURNINUS, TAMORA, DEMETRIUS, CHIRON, Lords, and others;
SATURNINUS with the arrows in his hand
that TITUS shot.
